# Shell is PowerShell on Windows

The integrated terminal is **PowerShell on Windows**. Unix/Git-Bash-only
commands are NOT available. Do not pipe to or call them.

## Not available — do not use

`tail`, `head`, `cat`, `grep`, `sed`, `awk`, `ls -la`, `which`, `rm -rf`,
`touch`, `export VAR=...`, `&&`-chained POSIX one-liners that assume bash.

## Use instead

| Goal | Don't | Do |
|------|-------|----|
| Last N lines | `... \| tail -40` | `... \| Select-Object -Last 40` |
| First N lines | `... \| head -20` | `... \| Select-Object -First 20` |
| Read a file | `cat file` | Use the Read tool (preferred) |
| Find in files | `grep foo` | Use the Grep tool (preferred) |
| Set env var | `export X=1` | `$env:X = "1"` |
| Chain commands | `a && b` | `a; b` or separate calls |

## Prefer tools over shell

For reading, searching, and editing files, use the dedicated tools (Read,
Grep, Glob, StrReplace) instead of shell commands. Reserve the terminal for
real system operations (npm, git, vitest, etc.).
